The paper deals with text-to-speech (TTS) synthesis, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with speech and audio processing. The paper also uses neural networks and generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely categories. The paper also involves optimization and performance evaluation, which are common in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category. Finally, cs.SD is repeated as the fifth category because it is the most specific and relevant category for this paper.
